            <biogHist>
                <p>John was born to John MacPherson and Marion MacPherson née McPhee in Kentangaval,
                    Barra. His mother died in childbirth. By the 1871 he was already a widow to
                    Catherine MacPherson and had been a corporal in the army. He was living in
                    Kentangaval with his four children Ann (20), Mary (18), Marion (16) and
                    Catherine (14), and his married sister Catherine (54). The three eldest
                    daughters were working as domestic servants. By 1881, only his son, Donald (21),
                    daughter Catherine (or Cattine), and grandson John McLachlan were living with
                    him; both he and his son were fishermen. </p>
                <p>John died in Kentangaval  from serious debility paralysis and his daughter
                    Catherine signed the death certificate.</p>
                <p>John MacPherson met Carmichael in 1870 and he recited the song 'Gillean Gealu'
                    [Baby Boy] and the charm 'Eolas Beum Sula'.</p>
